From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local build <local@orangepi3b>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 05:00:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] drm: mipi-dsi: guard detach during host probe unwind

On the Orange Pi 3B RK3566 vendor 6.1 kernel, enabling the Raspberry
touchscreen DSI path can make the Rockchip DW MIPI DSI probe fail during
deferred probing. The DW host unregister path then walks child DSI devices
and calls mipi_dsi_detach() for a device whose host pointer has already been
cleared. mipi_dsi_detach() dereferences dsi->host unconditionally and oopses:

  pc : mipi_dsi_detach+0x14/0x60
  Call trace:
    mipi_dsi_detach
    mipi_dsi_host_unregister
    dw_mipi_dsi_remove
    dw_mipi_dsi_rockchip_probe
    deferred_probe_work_func

Treat a missing DSI device, missing host, bogus low host pointer, or already
detached device as an already-detached device. This keeps the failed probe path
from taking the whole system down and lets the real DSI probe error be reported.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_mipi_dsi.c | 12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_mipi_dsi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_mipi_dsi.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_mipi_dsi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_mipi_dsi.c
@@ -31,6 +31,7 @@
 #include <linux/pm_runtime.h>
 #include <linux/slab.h>
 
+#include <asm/memory.h>
 #include <drm/display/drm_dsc.h>
 #include <drm/drm_mipi_dsi.h>
 #include <drm/drm_print.h>
@@ -391,10 +392,18 @@ EXPORT_SYMBOL(mipi_dsi_attach);
  */
 int mipi_dsi_detach(struct mipi_dsi_device *dsi)
 {
-	const struct mipi_dsi_host_ops *ops = dsi->host->ops;
+	const struct mipi_dsi_host_ops *ops;
 
-	if (WARN_ON(!dsi->attached))
+	if (!dsi)
+		return -EINVAL;
+	if (!dsi->attached)
 		return -EINVAL;
+	if (!dsi->host)
+		return -EINVAL;
+	if ((unsigned long)dsi->host < PAGE_OFFSET)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	ops = dsi->host->ops;
 
 	if (!ops || !ops->detach)
 		return -ENOSYS;
-- 
